videos.description: Nicolas Batum finds a wide-open Serge Ibaka for the simple dunk early in the first quarter.

tracking.trackingName: NBA_One-Play (Batum feeds Ibaka for early two-handed flush) 2021/1/8 ESHEET

videos.headline: Batum feeds Ibaka for early two-handed flush

videos.description: After Paul George hits a 3-pointer from the corner, Steph Curry drains a catch-and-shoot 3-pointer of his own.
videos.headline: PG13, Steph trade 3-pointers

videos.description: Serge Ibaka dunks the ball and yells emphatically afterwards.

tracking.trackingName: NBA_One-Play (Ibaka throws down slam with authority) 2021/1/8 ESHEET

videos.headline: Ibaka throws down slam with authority

videos.description: After blocking a shot on one end of the court, James Wiseman sprints to the other end and throws down a dunk.

tracking.trackingName: NBA_One-Play (Wiseman controls both ends of court) 2021/1/8 ESHEET

videos.headline: Wiseman controls both ends of court

videos.description: Steph Curry drains the long 3-pointer with 1 second left as he pulls the Warriors within six points.

tracking.trackingName: NBA_One-Play (Steph heats up in 3rd, hits deep 3 with 1 second left) 2021/1/8 ESHEET

videos.headline: Steph heats up in 3rd, hits deep 3 with 1 second left

videos.description: Andrew Wiggins goes 1-on-1 and hits a 28-foot 3-pointer late in the fourth to get the Warriors bench on their feet.

tracking.trackingName: NBA_One-Play (Wiggins drains cold-blooded 3-pointer late in 4th) 2021/1/8 ESHEET

videos.headline: Wiggins drains cold-blooded 3-pointer late in 4th

videos.description: Steph Curry heats up in the third and fourth quarters as the Warriors outscore the Clippers 64-40 in the second half on the way to a 115-105 win.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NBA Highlight (Steph's 38 fuels Warriors to comeback win vs. Clippers) 2021/1/8 ESHEET SOTFULL

videos.headline: Steph's 38 fuels Warriors to comeback win vs. Clippers

videos.description: Steph Curry, Draymond Green and the Warriors clap it up for Fred Kast after his final game keeping score for the team after a 58-year career.
